    <title>Research Technologist</title>
    <content>The Research Technologist position will be responsible for a variety of complex investigative procedures, assist in experimental design and development of new methods, tabulation and statistical analysis of data, preparation of manuscripts and grant proposals.

The incumbent will also be responsible for extraction of analytes from solid and aqueous matrices, performing laboratory management duties, operation,calibration and maintenance of advanced analytical instrumentation, training students, post-doc's, visiting scientists and other industry technicians in lab procedures and the use of analytical instruments, oversee general laboratory inventory and responsible for safety training and record-keeping. 
</content>
