Represent the Office of the Associate Dean at meetings within the College and University. Exercise professional judgement; make informed decision related to management policies and College business operations. Perform duties on behalf of the Associate Dean for Undergraduate Programs and Student Services and provide administrative support to Undergraduate Programs within the Office of the Associate Dean for Undergraduate Programs and Student Services. Manage and document office expenditures, coordinate meetings and workshops, maintain accurate records and compile reports. Serve as the primary operational and administrative contact for internal and external constituencies.

Develop and prepare materials under the direction of the Associate Dean related to undergraduate programs. Track and coordinate changes on all VCEA Undergraduate program-related Web pages. Provide information related to undergraduate programs and advising to prospective students, families, and external constituents; coordinate with appropriate offices and disbursing requested information. Participate as an advisor and representative of VCEA Undergraduate Programs at University Orientation and Visitation programs. 
