    <content>The School of Hospitality Business Management (SHBM) at Washington State University is seeking two (2) qualified applicants for two (2) full-time, tenure-track teaching positions to begin August 16, 2016 at the rank of assistant or associate professor, depending on qualifications, with demonstrated research and lodging-industry experience. Positions will be housed on the Everett campus, and will be primarily responsible for delivering courses for Everett, via on-line and other cutting edge distance teaching methods on a flexible schedule. This may include course delivery to other urban campuses or Pullman via videoconference, and/or online. Some travel to urban campuses, and/or Pullman may be required. 
Responsibilities include, but are not limited to: 
 • Teaching four (4) undergraduate courses, and/or graduate courses per year (assigned in fall, spring, or summer) in the area of hospitality business management. Courses will be taught face-to-face, online and via streaming. Students may be in Pullman, Vancouver, Everett, Tri-Cities, Brig, or elsewhere around the globe.   

