    <content>Duties include research, teaching, and service. The successful candidate should strengthen existing ties and cultivate new collaborations between CEE and other programs and centers, including: the State of Washington Water Research Center; the WSU Stormwater Center; the growing environmental program at WSU Vancouver; and the Center for Environmental Research, Education, and Outreach (CEREO). The candidate will also be expected to teach in areas of environmental engineering and chemistry at both the undergraduate and graduate levels, and to enhance the curriculum in environmental engineering.</content>
