    <content>This position manages and coordinates the day to day administrative functions and serves as the primary point of contact for several programs and projects at WSU North Puget Sound at Everett (WSU NPSE).  This includes     1) Serving as the lead for the transition of the Everett University Center to the new WSU Everett building.  This includes supervising the move, addressing departmental and partner needs and problem solving issues for faculty, staff and students and ongoing administration to ensure that academic programs are functioning smoothly. 2) Coordinating implementation of the plan and ongoing development and administration for the new medical campus at WSU NPSE including accreditation, implementation of the strategic plan, development of policies, procedures and processes related to the new medical campus, development of the medical campus budget and providing ongoing administrative support.        3) Coordinating development and the ongoing administration of the JC Dream research program at WSU North Puget Sound at Everett.  This includes coordination of meetings, travel and events related to the program and serving as the liaison between Pullman and WSU NPSE.  This position reports to the Senior Advisor to President Bernardo and provides high-level administrative support to the Senior Advisor.  They must exercise independent judgement, have the ability to act independently under delegated authority, to ensure successful implementation of the above programs and projects. </content>
