    <content>The Web/Drupal Software Developer will be responsible for the information technology development and support of a Drupal-based, open-source software project that is used nationally and globally for storage, data mining and visualization of scientific data related to genomics, genetics and breeding. Major responsibilities include  support of software, participation in planning and design meetings, solving systems problems, and interacting with other project developers.
The bioinformatics lab (www.bioinfo.wsu.edu) of Dr. Dorrie Main at Washington State University in Pullman, WA, is looking to recruit in a number of key computational positions. The Main Lab develops online genomic, genetic and breeding databases and tools to facilitate world-wide crop improvement efforts that address issues associated with response to food security and environmental change. The successful candidates will be joining a well-resourced, dynamic team who enjoy the benefits of a more flexible schedule within an academic research environment.
